# Implementation Plan: Sovereign Sentinel Hyper-Proxy (SSHP) & Cognitive Session Handoff (CSH) "Baton Pass" Protocol

This document outlines the high-fidelity implementation plan for integrating advanced visual/DOM PII masking, Sacred Covenant checking, and multi-agent human-in-the-loop session handoffs into the PRISM core dashboard.

## 📜 Architectural Goals & Security Boundary
1. **Zero-Trust Visual Redaction (SSHP)**: Redact all personal identifiable information (PII) including emails, password fields, credit cards, and SSNs from the page DOM *and* from the visual screenshot *before* they leave the sandbox or are sent to third-party LLMs.
2. **Sacred Covenant Auditing**: Verify browser actions (navigating, clicking, typing, script execution) against the `PrismCovenant` policies, blocking and escalating unsafe actions.
3. **Cognitive Session Handoff (CSH)**: Enable seamless session serialization, voluntary/preemptive "Baton Passing" to humans or security agents, and visual-headed human-in-the-loop (HITL) resumption.

---

## 🛡️ User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Use of Sharp for Visual Redaction**
> We will use `sharp` (already present in `package.json` dependencies) to dynamically draw black redaction rectangles over bounding boxes of sensitive input elements on screen. This process happens entirely in-memory on the host before saving or transmitting screenshots.

> [!WARNING]
> **Playwright StorageState Extension**
> Playwright's default `context.storageState()` captures cookies and localStorage, but does *not* capture sessionStorage. We will extend this by running an in-page script evaluation during serialization to capture and restore sessionStorage.

