## 🛠️ Proposed Changes

We will group our implementation into three core areas: the SSHP Core Engine (Phase B), the CSH "Baton Pass" Protocol (Phase C), and the integration points inside `dashboard-service.ts` and `autonomous-agent-loop.ts`.

### 1. Security & Redaction (Phase B)

#### [NEW] [sshp-interceptor.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/sshp-interceptor.ts)
Contains the `SSHPInterceptor` class responsible for:
- Parsing DOM trees to find sensitive elements: input elements matching `type="password"`, sensitive auto-completes, names containing `cvv`, `card`, `ssn`, `social-security`, etc.
- Matching text content for general PII formats (regex filters for emails, credit cards, SSNs).
- Calculating element bounding box coordinates relative to the viewport.
- Redacting DOM snapshot strings (replacing values with `[REDACTED_PII]`).
- Overlaying black rectangles on screenshot PNG buffers using `sharp` based on coordinate metadata.
- Querying the active `PrismCovenant` to validate commands before they execute.

```typescript
export class SSHPInterceptor {
  // Methods for sanitizing DOM, redacting screenshots via sharp, and validating against Covenant
  async sanitizeDom(rawHtml: string): Promise<{ sanitizedHtml: string; selectorsToMask: string[] }>;
  async redactScreenshot(imageBuffer: Buffer, selectorsToMask: string[], page: any): Promise<Buffer>;
  async auditAction(command: string, args: Record<string, any>): Promise<{ allowed: boolean; reason?: string }>;
}
```

### 2. Cognitive Session Handoff (Phase C)

#### [NEW] [csh-manager.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/csh-manager.ts)
Contains `CSHManager` class responsible for:
- Serializing full browser context: Playwright cookies, localStorage, and sessionStorage.
- Saving/loading the session package (`CognitiveHandoffState`) including complete agent reasoning logs, completed plans, and DAG memory.
- Exposing clean APIs to save handoff states to the workspace storage and restoring them into live Playwright instances.

```typescript
export class CSHManager {
  async serialize(page: any, context: any, reason: string, target: string): Promise<CognitiveHandoffState>;
  async deserialize(state: CognitiveHandoffState, page: any, context: any): Promise<void>;
}
```

### 3. Server Endpoints & Runtime Integration

#### [MODIFY] [dashboard-service.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/dashboard-service.ts)
- Integrate SSHP hooks inside `/api/browser/screenshot`, `/api/browser/click`, `/api/browser/type`, and `/api/browser/dom-snapshot` endpoints.
- Register new routes:
  - `POST /api/v1/autonomous/session/handoff`: Initiates session state packaging, changes state to `suspended`, and broadcasts a WebSocket handoff event.
  - `POST /api/v1/autonomous/session/resume`: Reloads state into the active browser and resumes autonomous execution.
  - `GET /api/v1/autonomous/session/pending`: Lists pending handoffs waiting for operator intervention.

#### [MODIFY] [autonomous-agent-loop.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/runtime/autonomous-agent-loop.ts)
- Add new FSM state support for `suspended` and `handing_off`.
- Enhance the goal loop execution sequence so that if it encounters an auth wall or CAPTCHA, it calls the `handoff` sequence and yields control gracefully, ready for manual operator resumption.

